      "*": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p><b><a href=\"/Main_Page\" title=\"Main Page\">Home</a> * <a href=\"/People\" title=\"People\">People</a> * John Roycroft</b>\n</p>\n<div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:302px;\"><a href=\"/File:JohnRoycroft1988inSaxony.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/4c/JohnRoycroft1988inSaxony.jpg/330px-JohnRoycroft1988inSaxony.jpg\" width=\"300\" height=\"226\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/4c/JohnRoycroft1988inSaxony.jpg/500px-JohnRoycroft1988inSaxony.jpg 1.5x, https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/4/4c/JohnRoycroft1988inSaxony.jpg 2x\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/File:JohnRoycroft1988inSaxony.jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>John Roycroft, 1988 <sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup></div></div></div> \n<p><b>Arthur John Roycroft</b>, (born July 25, 1929)<br />\nan English chess <a href=\"/Chess_Problems,_Compositions_and_Studies\" title=\"Chess Problems, Compositions and Studies\">endgame study composer</a>, international judge, and author. He is co-founder and member of the Chess Endgame Study Circle, founded on March 16, 1965, publishing the studies magazine <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/EG_%28magazine%29\">End Game (EG)</a> <sup id=\"cite_ref-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> . Roycroft was its publisher for the first 102 issues, from July 1965 until 1991. \nSince then, the <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Flemish\">Dutch-Flemish</a> ARVES, the <i><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Alexander_Rueb\">Alexander Rueb</a> Vereniging voor Schaakeindspelstudie</i> <sup id=\"cite_ref-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup> has been publisher, but Roycroft stayed as editor-in-chief until 2007, superseded by <a href=\"/Harold_van_der_Heijden\" title=\"Harold van der Heijden\">Harold van der Heijden</a> <sup id=\"cite_ref-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup>. Roycroft's adaptation of the <a href=\"/Richard_K._Guy\" title=\"Richard K. Guy\">Guy</a>–<a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hugh_Blandford\">Blandford</a> code in the 70s resulted in the <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/GBR_code\">GBR code</a>, an efficient way to index any chess position, in particular endgame studies <sup id=\"cite_ref-5\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup>. \n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><div class=\"toctitle\"><h2>Contents</h2></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#Endgame_Tablebases\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Endgame Tablebases</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#Selected_Publications\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Selected Publications</span></a>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#1970_...\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2.1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">1970 ...</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#1980_...\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2.2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">1980 ...</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-5\"><a href=\"#1990_...\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2.3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">1990 ...</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-6\"><a href=\"#External_Links\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">External Links</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-7\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h1><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Endgame_Tablebases\">Endgame Tablebases</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=John_Roycroft&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: Endgame Tablebases\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h1>\n<p>John Roycroft advised <a href=\"/Ken_Thompson\" title=\"Ken Thompson\">Ken Thompson</a> in <a href=\"/Endgame_Tablebases\" title=\"Endgame Tablebases\">endgame tablebases</a> generation with four and five pieces. \nFor queen and pawn against queen he published some results in 1986, years ahead of full tablebase output on CD <sup id=\"cite_ref-6\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup> <sup id=\"cite_ref-7\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-7\">&#91;7&#93;</a></sup> .\n</p>\n<h1><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Selected_Publications\">Selected Publications</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=John_Roycroft&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: Selected Publications\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h1>\n<p><sup id=\"cite_ref-8\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-8\">&#91;8&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"1970_...\">1970 ...</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=John_Roycroft&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" title=\"Edit section: 1970 ...\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li> <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">John Roycroft</a> (<b>1972</b>). <i>Test tube chess</i>. Stackpole Books</li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"1980_...\">1980 ...</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=John_Roycroft&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" title=\"Edit section: 1980 ...\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li> <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">John Roycroft</a> (<b>1981</b>). <i>The Chess Endgame Study</i>. <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dover_Publications\">Dover Publications</a></li>\n<li> <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">John Roycroft</a> (<b>1983</b>). <i>A Prophecy Fulfilled</i>. <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/EG_%28magazine%29\">EG</a>, Vol. V, No. 74</li>\n<li> <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">John Roycroft</a> (<b>1984</b>). <i>The GBR code</i>. <a href=\"/ICGA_Journal#7_1\" title=\"ICGA Journal\">ICCA Journal, Vol. 7, No. 1</a> <sup id=\"cite_ref-9\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-9\">&#91;9&#93;</a></sup></li>\n<li> <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">John Roycroft</a> (<b>1984</b>). <i>Two Bishops against Knight</i>. <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/EG_%28magazine%29\">EG</a>, Vol. 5, No. 75</li>\n<li> <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">John Roycroft</a> (<b>1984</b>). <i>A Proposed Revision of the ‘50-Move Rule’</i>. <a href=\"/ICGA_Journal#7_3\" title=\"ICGA Journal\">ICCA Journal, Vol. 7, No. 3</a></li>\n<li> <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">John Roycroft</a> (<b>1985</b>). <i>Chess-Endgame Data-Base`Oracles': Necessary and Desirable Features</i>. <a href=\"/ICGA_Journal#8_2\" title=\"ICGA Journal\">ICCA Journal, Vol. 8, No. 2</a></li>\n<li> <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">John Roycroft</a>, <a href=\"/Ken_Thompson\" title=\"Ken Thompson\">Ken Thompson</a> (<b>1986</b>). <i>Queen and Pawn on a2 against Queen</i>. Chess Endgame Consultants and Publishers, London</li>\n<li> <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">John Roycroft</a>, <a href=\"/Ken_Thompson\" title=\"Ken Thompson\">Ken Thompson</a> (<b>1986</b>). <i>Queen and Pawn on a6 against Queen</i>. Chess Endgame Consultants and Publishers, London</li>\n<li> <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">John Roycroft</a>, <a href=\"/Ken_Thompson\" title=\"Ken Thompson\">Ken Thompson</a> (<b>1986</b>). <i>Queen and Pawn on b7 against Queen</i>. Chess Endgame Consultants and Publishers, London</li>\n<li> <a href=\"/Jaap_van_den_Herik\" title=\"Jaap van den Herik\">Jaap van den Herik</a> (<b>1986</b>). <i>Roycroft's 5-Man Chess Endgame Series</i>. <a href=\"/ICGA_Journal#9_3\" title=\"ICGA Journal\">ICCA Journal, Vol. 9, No. 3</a></li>\n<li> <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">John Roycroft</a> (<b>1987</b>). <i>Expert Against Oracle</i>. <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.doc.ic.ac.uk/~shm/MI/mi11.html\">Machine Intelligence 11</a></li>\n<li> <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">John Roycroft</a> (<b>1987</b>). <i>The Experimental Positions of Ideas in Knowledge Synthesis</i>. <a href=\"/ICGA_Journal#10_2\" title=\"ICGA Journal\">ICCA Journal, Vol. 10, No. 2</a></li>\n<li> <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">John Roycroft</a> (<b>1989</b>). <i>The Computer is at it again - Interfering with the Endgame!</i> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/British_Chess_Magazine\">Britisch Chess Magazine</a>, Vol. 109, No. 10</li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"1990_...\">1990 ...</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=John_Roycroft&amp;action=edit&amp;section=5\" title=\"Edit section: 1990 ...\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li> <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">John Roycroft</a> (<b>1990</b>). <i>How to Treat Endgame Databases.</i> <a href=\"/ICGA_Journal#13_2\" title=\"ICGA Journal\">ICCA Journal, Vol. 13, No. 2</a></li>\n<li> <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">John Roycroft</a> (<b>1990</b>). <i>Identifying Three Types of Zugzwang</i>. <a href=\"/ICGA_Journal#13_4\" title=\"ICGA Journal\">ICCA Journal, Vol. 13, No. 4</a></li>\n<li> <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">John Roycroft</a> (<b>1991</b>). <i>A Postscript to the Computer's Involvement</i>. <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/British_Chess_Magazine\">Britisch Chess Magazine</a>, Vol. 111, No. 2</li>\n<li> <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">John Roycroft</a> (<b>1991</b>). <i>A Side-Effect of new Database Knowledge</i>. <a href=\"/ICGA_Journal#14_3\" title=\"ICGA Journal\">ICCA Journal, Vol. 14, No. 3</a></li>\n<li> <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">John Roycroft</a> (<b>1991</b>). <i>A Use for Endgame Databases?</i> <a href=\"/ICGA_Journal#14_4\" title=\"ICGA Journal\">ICCA Journal, Vol. 14, No. 4</a></li>\n<li> <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">John Roycroft</a>, <a href=\"/Don_Beal\" title=\"Don Beal\">Don Beal</a> (<b>1991</b>). <i>To Make Dumb Endgame Databases Speak</i>. <a href=\"/Advances_in_Computer_Chess_6\" title=\"Advances in Computer Chess 6\">Advances in Computer Chess 6</a></li>\n<li> <a href=\"/Richard_K._Guy\" title=\"Richard K. Guy\">Richard K. Guy</a>, <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">John Roycroft</a>, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://plus.google.com/108830667476351401818/about\">Kenneth Solja</a> (<b>1996</b>). <i><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.worldcat.org/title/richard-guys-chess-endgame-studies/oclc/037231061\">Richard Guy's Chess Endgame Studies</a></i>. Prime Actions </li></ul>\n<h1><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"External_Links\">External Links</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=John_Roycroft&amp;action=edit&amp;section=6\" title=\"Edit section: External Links\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h1>\n<ul><li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/John_Roycroft\">John Roycroft from Wikipedia</a></li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.linkedin.com/pub/john-roycroft/7/636/162\">John Roycroft | LinkedIn</a></li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://chesscomposers.blogspot.de/2012/07/july-25th.html\">Chess Composers | Arthur John Roycroft</a></li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.gadycosteff.com/eg/eg.html\">EG issues 1-152</a></li></ul>\n<h1><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=John_Roycroft&amp;action=edit&amp;section=7\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h1>\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-1\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">John Roycroft in the <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Elbe_Sandstone_Mountains\">Elbe Sandstone Mountains</a> (<a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Saxony\">Saxony</a>), during a trip of the participants of a chess course held 1988 in <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dresden\">Dresden</a>. Photo by <a href=\"/Rainer_Staudte\" title=\"Rainer Staudte\">Rainer Staudte</a>, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wikimedia_Commons\">Wikimedia Commons</a></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-2\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.gadycosteff.com/eg/eg.html\">EG issues 1-152</a></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-3\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-3\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.arves.org/English/index.htm\">Alexander Rueb Vereniging voor SchaakEindspelStudie - Dutch-Flemish Association for Endgame Study</a></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-4\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-4\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/EG_%28magazine%29\">EG (magazine) from Wikipedia</a></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-5\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-5\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"> <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">John Roycroft</a> (<b>1984</b>). <i>The GBR code</i>. <a href=\"/ICGA_Journal#7_1\" title=\"ICGA Journal\">ICCA Journal, Vol. 7, No. 1</a></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-6\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-6\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/John_Roycroft\">John Roycroft from Wikipedia</a></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-7\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-7\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a href=\"/Jaap_van_den_Herik\" title=\"Jaap van den Herik\">Jaap van den Herik</a> (<b>1986</b>). <i>Roycroft's 5-Man Chess Endgame Series</i>. <a href=\"/ICGA_Journal#9_3\" title=\"ICGA Journal\">ICCA Journal, Vol. 9, No. 3</a></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-8\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-8\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a href=\"/ICGA_Journal#RefDB\" title=\"ICGA Journal\">ICGA Reference Database</a></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-9\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-9\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/GBR_code\">GBR code from Wikipedia</a></span>\n</li>\n</ol></div>\n<p><b><a href=\"/People\" title=\"People\">Up one level</a></b>\n</p>\n<!-- \nNewPP limit report\nCached time: 20260301040954\nCache expiry: 86400\nDynam